SIMPLE: phosphorescence
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phosphorescence
<hw>Phos`phor*es"cence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>phosphorescence</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state
of being phosphorescent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The process of phosphorescing, especially that of
emitting light after a source of excitation has been removed. This
contrasts with the process of <contr>fluorescence</contr>, in which a
substance emits light of a lower wavelength than the illuminating light,
only while the illumination continues.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Light emitted by the process of
phosphorescence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phosphorescent</ent>⟦br⟧
